"n.演艺精湛的人 【英】 n.演艺精湛的人(a person who has great skill at some endeavor) 【考】 virtuoso : skill / potentate : power(艺术家要有技能/当 权者要有权利)反义词：mediocrity( 平庸之才) 【记】 virtu(好，美德)+oso 【例】 a virtuoso at the violin n. (功力深厚、技巧娴熟或有个人风格的)音乐师; 艺术名家 【记】virtu = virtue(n 美德; 优点), oso: 音乐师 【类】virtuoso: skill = potentate: power艺术家有技能 = 当权者有权利 【反】beginner(n 初学者) 【记】virtue so 如此有德行的人，大德之士，常用来称呼艺术名家，有德行涵养的人往往是真正技巧精湛的大师 virtuoso (n.)  1610s, ""scholar, connoisseur,"" from Italian virtuoso (plural virtuosi), noun use of adjective meaning ""skilled, learned, of exceptional worth,"" from Late Latin virtuosus (see virtuous). Meaning ""person with great skill, one who is a master of the mechanical part of a fine art"" (as in music) is first attested 1743."
